1
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,320
The supplies we are going to deliver

2
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,979
are more important than ever.

3
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,460
So we must carefully deliver these supplies to the frontline.

4
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,780
The soldiers at the frontline

5
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,850
are waiting for these medicines to save their lives.

6
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:00,760
Do you understand?

7
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,490
Understood.

8
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,480
Why have you been following him?

9
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,440
Yiyi,

10
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,880
this person is absolutely useful for my project.

11
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:35,760
Catch up with him and ask for advice.

12
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:38,120
I think you are obsessed with research.

13
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:38,040
Don't you look at the traffic lights when crossing the road?

14
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,200
You two are?

15
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,530
Traffic lights.

16
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,060
My name is Song Yao.

17
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,240
This is my best friend Zhang Yiyi.

18
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:48,970
Best friend?

19
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:49,440
Yes.

20
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:51,520
What's wrong with best friends?

21
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:53,520
No,

22
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,980
the headlights were really bright just now.

23
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:59,690
I told you to look at the traffic lights, not the headlights.

24
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,960
You were standing in the middle of the road.

25
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:06,040
The driver flashing the lights was already warning you.

26
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,970
But I didn't hear the horn just now.

27
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,160
This is the city,

28
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,720
honking is prohibited.

29
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,530
Are you from the mountains?

30
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,080
Stop at the red light, go at the green light.

31
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,740
Do you still need to be taught?

32
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:18,680
You just said

33
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,120
you are a Nanyang Overseas Chinese mechanic,

34
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,050
returning to transport supplies.

35
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,920
Nanyang Overseas Chinese mechanics returning

36
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,120
to serve the country.

37
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,240
This guy is really deep in character.

38
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,320
What era is this?

39
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,650
Still fighting the war?

40
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,720
Are you really a Nanyang Overseas Chinese mechanic?

41
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,600
But thank you both for saving me just now.

42
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,920
I have important tasks,

43
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,980
I'll take my leave.

44
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:38,880
Hey,

45
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,659
what are you doing?

46
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,770
Don't you think he's weird?

47
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,130
I think you're even weirder right now.

48
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,200
Aren't you curious about what he wants to do?

49
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,920
Why should I be curious about him?

50
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,580
What does it have to do with me?

51
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,920
I thought he was weird from the beginning,

52
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,640
saying nonsensical things.

53
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:59,020
What era is this? Still fighting the war?

54
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,320
No, I have to go see.

55
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,400
Hey,

56
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,400
Yaoyao.

57
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:10,880
Hello.

58
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,090
What do you need?

59
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:12,960
I need Quinine pills,

60
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:13,600
hemostatic bandages,

61
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,120
and that...

62
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,600
Excuse me, can you let me pass?

63
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,520
The child has a fever.

64
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,920
What's the temperature?

65
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,600
Get a cooling patch along with the medicine.

66
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,040
Do I pay for the medicine here?

67
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,640
Thank you.

68
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,920
I need Quinine pills,

69
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,120
hemostatic bandages,

70
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,200
and Sulfanilamide powder.

71
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,720
Quinine pills are an old medicine.

72
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,450
Out of stock.

73
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,520
There are better ones than Quinine pills.

74
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,360
Come, give it to me.

75
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:32,800
Quick.

76
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:34,840
This.

77
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,320
Better than Quinine pills?

78
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,050
Are you sure?

79
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,020
One pill is 10 times stronger.

80
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,159
10 times.

81
00:05:41,159 --> 00:05:41,960
Yeah.

82
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,000
How much do you have?

83
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,460
What symptoms do you have?

84
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:46,720
Hanwen.

85
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,400
Don't talk nonsense.

86
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,560
Hold on.

87
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:55,000
These bastards are still bombing so vigorously.

88
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,480
I didn't expect

89
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,520
the deadly thing

90
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,520
wasn't the Japs' bombing.

91
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,160
We've made it through so many times.

92
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,820
We definitely will this time.

93
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,560
Once we pass this bamboo forest,

94
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,820
I'll find you a doctor.

95
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,650
Give me 10 trucks first.

96
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,560
Hurry, I can't wait.

97
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,960
10 trucks?

98
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,440
This is my work ID.

99
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:24,520
Take a look.

100
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,440
The store doesn't have that much stock.

101
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,120
You have to go to the factory,

102
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,200
and you need certificates and vouchers.

103
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,480
No, I'm really in a hurry.

104
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,800
Can you just give it to me first?

105
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,640
We don't have that much stock.

106
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:33,520
I'm really in a hurry.

107
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,680
Just give me what you have, okay?

108
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,960
The store doesn't have that much stock.

109
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:38,159
You need a prescription and certificate.

110
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:38,880
Sorry.

111
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:39,720
This is a misunderstanding.

112
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,320
Sorry.

113
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,520
Come with me.

114
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,600
Crazy.

115
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:49,700
What are you doing?

116
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:54,080
ID.

117
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,930
You can buy medicine with this?

118
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:01,880
Yaoyao.

119
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,730
Is this what you want to see?

120
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:14,640
Yiyi.

121
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:15,960
Didn't you say you were hungry?

122
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,480
Let's go eat together.

123
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:18,500
Not hungry.

124
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,240
I'm not the one whose stomach is growling.

125
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,100
I'm not eating.

126
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,880
What exactly do you want?

127
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:23,760
Give me the ID.

128
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,010
Nothing, just having a meal

129
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,820
and chatting about your work.

130
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,800
Why would you invite him to eat for nothing?

131
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,080
Why do you care so much?

132
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,080
Okay.

133
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,480
Do whatever you want.

134
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,400
We met by chance.

135
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,040
Why would I eat with you?

136
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,960
Your stomach is growling,

137
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,490
yet you're still stubborn.

138
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,360
We'll be familiar after eating.

139
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:47,890
Let's go.

140
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,680
Give me the ID.

141
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,720
Are you really inviting him to eat?

142
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,760
Ah.

143
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:54,760
Song Yao.
